main event: An unidentified flying object was reported near Syracuse, New York on 5 March 1953.
interesting points: The object was described as a bicycle type with holes on the sides and flashing a yellow light., The sighting was reported for the third time by the observer., The object was not tracked on radar at any time during the observation., The weather conditions at the time of the sighting were unknown., The report concluded that the details were insufficient for evaluation.
sighted object: bicycle type object with holes and a flashing yellow light
witness description: Only one source provided the observation, and the authenticity remains unknown.
